                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/19.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Vice Consul <persName type="to">Bowman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-04-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch No. 230
                    of April 12, 1913, with regard to the payment of taxes on mining claims in
                    Sonora owned by Americans.</p>
                <p>In this connection your attention is referred to the Department’s telegram of
                    April 26, 1913, [to Vice Consul Simpich] upon the subject.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
